Sometimes life feels like one of those children's Donald Duck comics where every panel directly follows the previous one so like if their uncle warns them the city is getting dangerous the ducklings will meet a thief on the next page, you just wonder who even wrote the script

Or like John Swartzwelder novels where detective Burly will read in the newspaper how people have been reporting seeing ghosts and then he immediately sees one on the street outside, just bizarrely "themed" days in your real life which feel like the scripted episode of a sitcom
I would avoid them and try to bribe/bullshit my way through, maybe you can say you already got it last year for travel or something

I like how Gunther Fehlinger is slowly turning into a phantom of the opera type figure for the Austrian parliament, haunting the halls, sneaking around some abandoned desolate corridor over the ceiling, watching politician meetings from some hole in the wall inside a secret room.

Shitting at midnight in a thin-walled building is always surreal because you hear an orchestra of most bizarre noises. Someone moaning, an argument, housefoid yelling all intelligibly on the tenth floor bathroom, more moans. Disorients you. But I keep shitting for Ray regardless.

At my ceramic post, listening to an entire building's laughter, crying, screaming, heavy thumps of objects and bodies being moved through space somewhere, fear grips my heart but I persist into the small hours of the night keeping watch as a nightguard of mine own digestion.
I guess it can make the bullshitting part a lot harder if it fails

Gunther Fehlinger the phantom of the Austrian parliament revealing himself to a young female staffer working deep into the small hours of the night in her office and leading her down a secret stairway into a 40s underground bunker in the bowels of the building full of V2 rockets.

Rowing her across a subterranean lake while teaching her how to start a war or declare the current government illegitimate using some Carlsbadian esoteric law legal loophole. Doesn't force her to marry him but just to become a member of one of his Montenegro-registered NGOs.
